content.detailedDescription:
I was driving eastward on cedar run road when i saw a perfectly spherical object made up of something that resembled mercury (very metallic and smooth - no doors or windows). it hovered for about four seconds then vanished. i did not see it vanish, but trees blocked my view for a few seconds and when i was in the line of sight again, it was gone. i noticed a plane just north of the area and another just south of the area - the planes were very small compared to the object. the object was about the size of the moon in the night sky, but the moon was not visible at the time of the sighting in that direction. 

i was very tired at the time of the sighting, but it was so vivid. because of the time of day, i'm really curious to know whether other people witnessed this.
content.summary: Large silver-metallic sphere hovering above city. present, then vanished.

content.detailedDescription: On the evening of july 4, 2015 approximately 9:06 pm, i was standing at the mobile station with my son located at 4801 laurel canyon blvd., valley village, ca to watch the fireworks.  to the west of the fireworks about 50 to 100 yards i observed an orange orb which was ascending, once it reached about 500 feet it started to head east at a 45 degree angle towards the fireworks.  moments before the object went through the fireworks the orb turned blue, as it was passing through the fireworks the orb became slightly obscured from the smoke.  as this was taking place a second orange orb looked like it jetted up from what appeared to be the los angeles river.   once in the general vicinity, the orb that had previously turned blue began hovering giving the appearance that it was waiting for the orange orb from the los angeles river to join it, moments later it did just that.   once the two orbs joined they went on a north by northeast trajectory which went directly over my son and i, then disappeared.  as i was observing this objects i felt there was a childlike curiosity, as if they were had wanted to observe the fireworks.
content.summary: Observed orange orb during fireworks, then turned blue.  after hovering for a few moments another orb joined the blue orb

content.summary: Looked like a cube that twirled

content.detailedDescription:
Had passed photogenic farm that is the subject of the photo on my way to pick up produce at another farm. decided to stop and take a couple of shots upon my return and took three images with a sigma sd15 dslr equipped with a zoom lens.  took two long shots and one tighter shot from the same spot beside the road and noticed nothing out of the ordinary.

after returning home later in the day, downloaded the digital files onto a macbook pro and converted the raw images to jpeg using sigma photopro6 software and performed some basic editing to sharpen overall image clarity and color vibrance using affinity1.3.4 image editing software. upon final review, i selected the tight shot as my favorite and was preparing to submit to an online literary magazine for potential publication when i noticed what appears to be a small circular object/defect on the image. 

normally, i would just chalk this up to lens schmutz, flare or aberration, but note that the object/defect seems to exhibit some reflectivity when viewed enlarged. 

note: object/defect is located above the forth power line down from the top of the image and right of the grain bin.
content.summary: What appears to be a disc shape object noticed while editing digital photo images.

content.detailedDescription: In car heading south just near broughton, scotland. saw matt black triangle, hovering just above trees. stopped car to observe ufo. opened window to look up. 2 flashing lights. craft was totally soundless. trees were not affected by the hovering of the craft. observed it for approximately 4 minutes, then craft accelerated exceedingly fast north, but again soundless with no air disturbance. never seen anything so close like this before. very obvious wasn't recognisable aircraft. trees weren't that high; so we had a good view of the craft. we felt very excited to have witnessed it. found it incredible, especially as there was no disturbance by it and completely soundless. the rate it left the scene was unbelievable! again no noise whatsoever and all around us was calm.
content.summary: Matt black triangle, soundless, hovering treeline, car underneath observing, 2 flashing lights, extremely fast acceleration without sound or disturbance

content.detailedDescription:
I was walkin down my interior house stairs and saw what looked like a commercial aircraft at first. i've seen ufo's in this direction before so i watched closely. the object was a flat disc with mullticoloured lights flashing around it at random times. this was a hint that the aircraft was not an air plane. it flew from south to north at different speeds and then stopped. i was just about to run to get my camera when i heard a deep rumble and kept watching. the ufo started moving backwards and then stopped. after this, the object started moving slowly upwards straight into the sky and then suddenly darted directly up and i lost sight of it within 2 seconds. about 15 seconds after the ufo disappeared, i heard a very deep rumbling sound.

at this moment i didn't think much, but then it occured to me that i felt like someone was watching me. at the very moment i am writing this (10-15 mins after event) i keep constantly checking over my shoulder to see if anyone is there. i have seen ufo's before and this one was probably the second most beliveable one i've ever seen. another time a yellow disc hovered over my house for over 20 minutes. i called the local air forse base and they said a blip was showing on the radar and then disappeared less than 60 seconds into the call. i never wrote a complete report like this one.

i really hope others who saw this event do come foward and share their sighting as a report. i would love to see others backing up my sighting. i know i saw it, i know it was real. i have not taken any medication in the last month and have had no drugs since then either.

sorry if the drawing is unclear, i just had to do a quick sketch and i'm no artist.

then they would stop or just go out like a candle.We stayed for as long as we could approximately 30 min

content.detailedDescription: My family and i were taking a walk with a friend and her two children on monday, august 18th, 2015.  we started a little before sunset, but stayed out for almost two hours.  it was a very peaceful night with clear skies.  there was a plane that was flying very low, touching down at the air strip across the river in ohio, and then circling my town again and again.  i always like to watch airplanes and helicopters, so i was already looking at the sky. as daylight faded into night, i noticed another light in the sky.  at first, i thought that it was a plane.  however, i noticed that it was moving much too slow to be an airplane.  so, then i though that it must be a helicopter.  however, this was ruled out because the object was low enough that we would have heard it.  the children we were working with that that it was a fairy.  also, there was only one light - a fiery orange, and it wasn't blinking as you see planes and helicopters doing.  the object did not move much, but it did move a little, and primarily was in a straight line.  it moved in a south to south east direction from where we first saw it.  the sighting lasted anywhere from five to seven minutes.  there were times that the light would fade.  it could still be seen sometimes, though there was no light.  other times, it would turn it's light off, and then later it would come back on: it did this three or four times.  a few minutes later, we saw a helicopter on the horizon, and we lost sight of the object after it dimmed completely.  the experience left me feeling a bit strange, and somewhat paranoid.
content.summary: Monday august 18th around 9.30, orange light hovering over town for several minutes.

content.detailedDescription:
I am 67 years old and have never told anyone about this event due to possible ridicule, scorn, disbelief and/or loss of credibility. when i was 9 years old we lived in a rental farm house in the country (southern indiana). at that time, there were few farmhouses in the area as most of the countryside was tree covered with lots of vegetation. we did not have indoor plumbing and in fact we had to use an outhouse about 150 feet from the house. as was my usual routine, i needed to relieve myself very early in the morning. that morning, as i was opening the kitchen door, i looked up and was in shock as i witnessed a very large saucer shaped aircraft hovering over our farm house. i was terrified and immediately went upstairs and woke my mother. she did not believe me and thought i was imagining the craft. i can still vividly see in my minds eye the craft as it silently hovered about 100 feet over the house. it was clearly observable with approximately 3/4ths of the craft in open view. the remainder of the craft was not visible as it was obscured by the roof of our house. i once casually mentioned this event when i was in my 20's as a young army soldier. i was immediately laughed at and was called "hey ufo". i tried to mitigate the flack i was receiving and told the men i worked with (who i thought i could trust) that i was just kidding. so for years, i kept this to myself and filed it away.

2nd encounter:
btw, i am a retired us army veteran and while on active duty, had a top secret security clearance. i am now a career employee currently working for the federal government. i feel compelled to say this: i am telling this now because i do not want to go to my grave without doing so. at this point in my life i could care less if the whole world laughs at me. but you know what, it is true and i know what i saw. now, lets go forward to 1980. while stationed at the us military academy at west point ny, i was a member of the w.P. rod & gun club but i only fished. one beautiful saturday i had been fishing on a remote lake for much of the day. as the sun was setting, approx 7pm) i was on the lake by myself, fishing in the middle of the lake. all of a sudden, i got the strangest feeling that i've never had before. it was as though the hair on my neck was standing up and i sensed a tingling sensation all over. the feeling of emanate danger was all consuming to the point that i started to panic. i said to myself, what in the world is wrong with me and tried to shrug it off. the feeling persisted and as i looked at the high hills across the lake, i noticed an incredible fog bank. it appeared to be solid and had the appearance of mashed potatoes. again, i've fished this and surrounding lakes numerous times and never experienced such an event. this fog bank was like a curtain being drawn and was uniformly descending toward the lake. i immediately started my small motor and made a dash toward the dock. by the time i reached the dock, the fog had reached the far side of the lake but continued to come toward me. i left my fishing gear on the dock and ran to my van. i started the engine and floored the gas pedal. from round pond to the highway was about 3/4ths of a mile. when i was in sight of the highway, something flew over my van at a very high rate of speed. when it passed my van, a series of flashing lights (red/yellow/orange) flashed in through the windshield. it lit up my van and was gone in a flash. now that's my story. i did not then, nor do i now have an explanation of why these events happened but they did and i feel relieved that i've finally told it to someone who may believe me. thanks for allowing me to tell my accounts of these incidents.
content.summary: Opened door to go out to the outhouse, ufo hovering over house in country

content.detailedDescription: My 12 year old son and i took a detour on a country rd to avoid an interstate closure (i10w) to get home at 10pm. while driving on the dark rd, i observed several very bright lights approximatly 1 1/2 city blocks up the road right at the tree line. i said to my son "what the heck is that?" we both observed it as we drove closer to it going about 40mph. as we approached the lights a very large, black triangle shaped object became visible as we were no longer directly facing the lights. the object was not pointed like a spear, it was more elongated. the hight was about a city bus or perhaps a big thicker. the object was right next to the rd hovering or moving slowly forward directly over the tree line. as we were directly beside the object i slowed the car down, but did not stop, i looked at it as we passed it. it was black, no lights underneath and was completely silent. i had yet to process what i was looking at. as i passed it, i looked in my side mirror and the object had risen above the tree line a bit, and had a row of lights running across the entire length. the lights were white, but about 1/4 the brightness of the front lighrs. i asked my son "did you see that?" he said "yes!!" i again turned and looked back but the object was either gone or turned off the lights. i did not see the object fly away, it just wasnt there anymore. i asked my son "what did you see? he said "a huge black triangle!" he became frightened and did not want to turn around. we continued down the rd and did not see anything else. he described exactly what i saw without me describing first.
content.summary: Very large triangle craft observed at a very close distance by myself and 12 year old son

content.detailedDescription:
I was sleeping when i was awoken  (at app.3.30 am) by a screeching sound.  as i sat in my bed, the whole room filed with a bright lime colored light.

it toke me a second to move.  i ran to the window (view on downtown edmonton) to see for a second or two this huge ball racing over the downtown area.  it left no tail from friction but was very fast.  it was gone in seconds.

the next morning, as i got in my car, i always opened the radio for some music.  the disk jockey was talking about the sighting.  describing exactly what i had witnessed that night.  he also said that over 500 people called in that night to describe the same thing.

a few days later, a friend told me that the canadian air force said that a ufo had crossed alberta from south to north in only 15 minutes.

i have never heard of the incident since.
content.summary: Huge ball (app. 200 feet wide - from my point of view) - multiple fixed colors

content.detailedDescription: I was standing along side of my home, in my driveway on the evening of july 4, 2015 with my camera hoping to film fireworks air bursts. the sun had set but was not fully dark yet.  i was looking east in the direction of lake michigan.  the wind was slight and from the west.   as i looked east i saw a steady glow in the sky which i can only describe as a steady and constant glow similar to a glow that would be seen from a flashlight held above your head and pointing upward in a haze or fog with the lower edge of the glow having a distinct hard edge with no light beneath it.  the glow above that hard edge was constant, and the glow above that edge did not extend far above that hard edge- maybe as high above the object as it was wide but spanned the full 180 degrees above that hard edge on the bottom of the glow.  the object moved from the east toward my location west but never came as far west as my location so was never over head at any time.  at about a 75 degree angle the object softly  but distinctly changed direction and turned to the north and continued in that direction.  the object then started to slide back to the east a couple of degrees but continued moving north bound.  the luminosity of the light did not change as would the headlight of a car or airplane landing lights, which i routinely see as i am in a landing path for o'hare international airport and maintained the same glow despite the direction changes the object made.  essentially the light maintained the same glow it had moving toward me as it did moving away.  it appeared to be a single glow as there was only one point of light.  the object continue north-northeast and seemed to gain speed as it moved away out of view to the north.  the color of the glow had a slight orange hue to it but was generally white in color.  my first thought was that it was a bit strange in that it moved against the breeze, maintained a consistent glow and was absolutely silent.  there were a lot of fireworks going on but in between the booms, the object gave no sound which i also found very strange, all of which prompted me to point the camera in that direction.
content.summary: Glowing light that changed direction several times, remained constant and was silent.

content.detailedDescription:
Don't know the hr i went out(no smoking allowed in my home) to have a cigarette.Stood by front door looked up and out because i saw movement in the sky(been this way post9-11) well, i saw the first white oval light and then the long arm that had the blue & several pink lights moving. i wear glasses. thought maybe a reflection of street lights. i removed glasses rubbed my eyes. put glasses back on this thing is still moving coming from timber ridge over golf course and thru hemlock st. i decided whatever it was wanted to see it with my eyes removed glasses & went out to sidewalk. now i noticed the other two arms attached to this humungous black object moving in the stealth of night yet it was darker than the deep blue of the sky. no one was out walking that i could see. now i go out in to the middle of the street to watch where this thing is going. now i see a man walking his dog by hemlock and i run to him as this thing hover over my home & neighbors-we're connected townhouse and ask him if he see what i see. he looks up looks away looks back up & says"what the--". i've been looking for him-havent seen him since that nite. now it had a white oval light one on each arm and they were moving in sinq and i realized it was attached to the big black thing moving ( and not 3 helicopters flying in sinq-no chopper noise either) now it glides across springmeadow dr hovers a few seconds and glides to the right-and goes directly over my home & my neighbors and hovers there-i mentally said"oh no you don't"and thru my cigarette in my ashtray ran in my house and locked the doors and got under my cover on my couch. after recovering a few minutes from the realization of what i saw i clicked on tv went to news 12 li to see if any one had reported seeing anything.  there was nothing. i was so frightened and aim aware our gov't is involved with picking up these if they land. 
listen, please i work for the gov't & i have only told 4 people about my experience & i don't wish to have my boss or employees to know of this i keep a low profile!!!!!
before i forget-it sounded like a very large air conditioner like the one my office is located in. i don't stay out now after dark & have missed 2 outside concerts because there is no indoor place to go after dusk.   and don't discount the person who saw something as big as an 18 wheeler-it was bigger than that the whole sky was moving i am able to differentiate between human noises & this machine & the whole thing scared the willies out of me.  i lost sight of the object when it glided down ginger lane &   i ran in my house &  locked the doors all of them   that man i saw walking his dog-i haven't seen him since i would love to converse with him over our observance. i have been watching & looking before dusk every day. we had no other conversation as i ran back across the a street in shock & into my home. i didn't think to get his name.I would expect to hear about a sighting such as this out in nevada, or a desert somewhere---but in holbrook ny a heavily populated area???!!!!!!!! there also is a well, it is shaped & looks like a christmas tree with all green lights that is way up in the atmosphere-with the stars--near my home. listen either i need to get out of town or they need to go find another universe to haunt because this one belongs to humans & im not seeking to venture out & explore & this just really petrified me!!!! yes i've included emotion and feelings you asked& these are the facts as they occurred on thursday july 23rd 2015 sorry i didn't look at the clock before i went out   tell me if you can answer me this-why do they come in the stealth of night???? why won't they come in broad sunlight so all humans can see them- you see if it weren't for their lights we wouldn't know they were here unless you heard the steady drone of their object  if mufon has communication with these entities perhaps you would convey my message to them-let us live in peace-leave us humans alone!!!!
on a clear nite-no overcast/clouds you can see the christmas tree blinking & sometimes moving  please don't discount the person who was in ronkonkoma ny & saw it as big as an 18 wheeler--they described similar to what i saw our dates visualizing were not far apart & he's within 10-15 minutes from my home-so is maccarthur airport
i couldn't take any pictures because it happened so quickly & my cellphone was on charge.  i do have a sketch drawn on the 24th, but i don't know how to get it onto this to send you   if you call me i can send the sketch i drew with notes on it to your phone-i know how to do this  please don't come to my home-i don't want my neighbors alarmed & thinking i did something bad & having all these gov't people here .
